The paper deals with image synthesis using deep generative models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves a conditional U-Net and a variational autoencoder, which are both machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic latent representations, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve datasets related to fashion and objects, which are common topics in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
